dent and tactics/PvP skill play a big part.  SKs can be pretty rough in duels.  In general I think we have a few advantages, but again it really can vary.<br><br>If you can't see invis they have a big advantage.<br><br>If you don't watch your HPs close enough they can finish you off with a well-timed HT.<br><br>Jousting skill differences can make or break the battle.<br><br>Buffs/dispells/debuffs can also play a part.<br><br>I wouldn't say in general a level 60 SK can't beat a level 60 Paladin.  I'd say with equal gear/AA/skill it would be a pretty close fight. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Duke Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uignacius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ignacius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/6/02 9:15:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> `</span><hr size=1> Celestial Cleansing is un fricken beatable in pvp against melees.<br><br>You basically cant get interupted, and it heals like 700ish.<br><br>Now i have about 150ish wis and thats only 10% mana, so i can cast that at least 10 times, not counting if the paladin has any FT items and such, also factor in regen.<br><br>So thats roughly 7000hps in heals, Sk's do decent damage, but there is no way he is going to do that much damage to you before you kill him if you have similar gear.<br><br>The SK gets a lifetap at 60 that does i think around 250 in pvp for the same mana as celestial cleansing, with a 6.1 second cast time, which would be easy as fug to interupt.<br><br>Sk has some nice dots and such, but the pally will just outheal them, even if the sk wants to take the hits trying to cast them.  There biggest dot is only 690 in pve, so even less in pvp, and thats outhealed in one heal.<br><br>Your only real problem? timing your heals so that you dont get below 1k hps or youre dead instantly.  <br><br>But id have to say 60sk's are the hardest to fight for me personally, not counting rangers with am3 and endless quiver/ bards =p<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umemnenthmoondust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Memnenth Moondust</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 1432<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/6/02 10:29:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://fallenalliance.org/screenshots/cecil_20020408123732.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: `</span><hr size=1> Bards are impossible /cry.<br><br>Ive tried several times now.<br><br>They Sieve your mana away, then they put a huge DS on themselves, and decent regen, and just let you kill yourself, if they get low they run a bit at 40hp per tick regen.<br><br>Ive not dealt with an AM3 Ranger, but Id guess you are kited pretty well, not much you can do at that point.<br><br>SKs should fall pretty easily IMHO, CC &gt; all melee <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44702>Sir Memnenth </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useventhsword.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seventhsword</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/6/02 11:03:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: `</span><hr size=1> Killed hsadow knights before.  You don't need to be lvl 60 just smarter then the sk.  If you want to mess with the sk buy a invis potion or two.  They don't think paladins can invis so they willn't put see invis on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Mainly I'd worry about the sk's pet so spook undead should be up.  I'd fear the pet 1-2 x the whole battle.  mostly once in begining and again if you can't get a heal to stick.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uignacius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ignacius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/6/02 11:59:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> `</span><hr size=1> Pets are weak, rarely do sk's uses pets in pvp, in a duel all prepared i might see an sk use a pet, but its rather easy to root/fear it, and with slay 3 it would go down quick.<br><br>You cant count on invis potions because 90% of people on pvp servers have see invis items, and what exactly does going invis get you? besides a few seconds/minutes of not attacking, maybe you could get away sure, but thats not exactly the point is it?<br><br>I hate bards in general, all they do is just run around you and put on there crap ass dots and do like 2 bubs of damage in 30 minutes which is healed in a cast or 2.  Only truely uber bards who oos you, then proc tash orb/j stick and then snare you with uber melee, i would actually consider being afraid of. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table>